ta’ro mi ‘where?’ ta’ro leam ‘to where?’; ta’ro mihoʔ ‘from where?’
he’to mi refers to a direction not a location; emota =  ‘above’; tong = ‘high up’; pong = ‘down below’; hele = ‘downwards’; taʔle = ‘upwards’
hele’ho mi = ‘below overthere (different level)’; hepo mi = ‘below overthere (same level)’ efar= ‘under’
